df1$employ <- NA
df1$employ[df1$emp_length == "n/a"] <- "Unemployed"
df1$employ[df1$emp_length == "< 1 year"] <- "Less than 2 years"
df1$employ[df1$emp_length == "1 year"] <- "Less than 2 years"
df1$employ[df1$emp_length == "2 years"] <- "2-4 years"
df1$employ[df1$emp_length == "3 years"] <- "2-4 years"
df1$employ[df1$emp_length == "4 years"] <- "2-4 years"
df1$employ[df1$emp_length == "5 years"] <- "5-9 years"
df1$employ[df1$emp_length == "6 years"] <- "5-9 years"
df1$employ[df1$emp_length == "7 years"] <- "5-9 years"
df1$employ[df1$emp_length == "8 years"] <- "5-9 years"
df1$employ[df1$emp_length == "9 years"] <- "5-9 years"
df1$employ[df1$emp_length == "10+ years"] <- "10+ years"
df1$employ <- factor(df1$employ,
                      levels = c("Unemployed",
                                 "Less than 2 years",
                                 "2-4 years",
                                 "5-9 years",
                                 "10+ years"))

Here, the employee service duration(emp_length) is grouped as (Unemployed, Less than 2 years, 2-4 years, 5-9 years, 10+ years) _______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
